@/main.description: The main nodes of the project

@/change-the-value-of-the-item-to.description: Works together with "menu-item" via "ITEM IN" and "CHANGE" ports. Switches the value at the "Value'" output from "Val0" to "Val..." after the "CHANGE" signal. At the output "VALUE" is the number of the current value.

B1LH_1-La.label: ANY

SJyIRJZ8a.description: Input pulse. After each signal arrival, causes switching of VALUE' from VAL0 to VAL...;
SJyIRJZ8a.label: CHANGE

rkIull-La.description: The selected value. Equals to one of `VAL` input.
rkIull-La.label: VALUE'

must be connected to the "ITEM OUT" node

@/example.description: An example of implementing a menu for "PWM" control of "RGB" "LED" indicator, as an interface screen "LCD" 16x2. We control with two buttons, "Scroll" to change the item, "OK" to change the values ​​(0%to 100% after 100% is reset to 0%).

@/menu-item.description: NODE is a menu item that has its own name and is activated at the address. We connect them to each other and create a list of menus, each item of which responds to the OK signal at its address. At the output of the chain from these nodes will be the name of the one whose address was called.

rk7Px2KH6.description: the address to which the item is recalled
rk7Px2KH6.label: ADR

BkF7VhKr6.description: Exit to the display or to ANY other menu-item
BkF7VhKr6.label: ITEM

S1GhNnKBT.description: A menu item selection signal, for example from a button. It also causes an OK' pulse to appear at the output, changing the MEM trigger.
S1GhNnKBT.label: OK

SyahsnKBT.description: For connection to the inputs "ITEM IN" menu-value and change-the-value....

@/menu-value.description: This node is the value of the menu item, which can be increased by the ok signal to the limit, after which it will reset to 0. It works together with menu-item. The value will be displayed as a percentage. See all the details of the work in my-menu
